2007-11-21  ashuang

	* [r39] configure.in: added -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64
	  -D_LARGEFILE_SOURCE to CFLAGS
	* [r38] libcam/input_v4l2.c: forgot to modify input_v4l2 for new
	  stream_* behaviors
	* [r37] libcam/convert_colorspace.c, libcam/convert_to_rgb8.c,
	  libcam/convert_to_rgb8.h: modified convert_to_rgb8 unit to do
	  generic CamUnit wrapping rather than re-implementing conversion
	  routines. Added bayer support to convert_to_rgb8 via fast debayer
	  unit. added bgra->rgb conversion to convert_colorspace unit
	* [r36] libcam/convert_colorspace.c, libcam/convert_to_rgb8.c,
	  libcam/filter_bayer.c, libcam/filter_fast_bayer.c,
	  libcam/input_example.c, libcam/input_log.c, libcam/input_v4l.c,
	  libcam/unit.c, libcam/unit.h, plugins/dc1394/input_dc1394.c,
	  plugins/ladybug2/input_ladybug2.c: change CamUnit so that
	  cam_unit_stream_init, cam_unit_stream_on, cam_unit_stream_off,
	  cam_unit_stream_shutdown always do both error checking (that
	  CamUnit is in the required state, etc.) and the actual state
	  setting. Subclasses of CamUnit now simply return 0 if it is okay
	  to change state, and -1 if it is not.

